<html>
	<head>
		<title>GeoGuessr</title>
		<meta name="robots" content="noindex" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0, user-scalable=no" />

		<link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="favicon.ico">
		<style>
			body { background: #f3f3ef;font-family: arial; margin: 0; }
			ul { list-style-type: none; padding: 0 20px; }
			li { margin-top: 20px;}
			a { color: #000; }
			#header { display: block;height: 40px;background: #000;padding: 10px;}
			#container {
				display: block;
				margin-top: 50px;
				margin-left: auto;
				margin-right: auto;
				text-align: center;
			}

			#compass {
				margin-left: auto;
				margin-right: auto;
				background-image: url("data:image/png;base64,");

				background-size: 206px 206px;
				width: 206px;
				height: 206px;
			}

			#needle {
				width: 206px;
				height: 206px;
				-webkit-animation: spin 4s ease-in-out infinite;
				-moz-animation: spin 4s ease-in-out infinite;
				animation: spin 4s ease-in-out infinite;
			}
			@-moz-keyframes spin { 100% { -moz-transform: rotate(540deg); } }
			@-webkit-keyframes spin { 100% { -webkit-transform: rotate(540deg); } }
			@keyframes spin { 100% { -webkit-transform: rotate(540deg); transform:rotate(540deg); } }
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<div id="header">
			<a href="/">
				<img alt="GeoGuessr" width="170" src="data:image/png;base64," />
			</a>
		</div>
		<div id="container">
			<h1>Did the world stop spinning or what?!</h1>
			<div id="compass">
				<img id="needle" src="data:image/png;base64," />
			</div>
			<br />
			<p>The page you were looking for could not be found.</p>
		</div>
	</body>
</html>
